  "prompt": "If I live in NYC but work on Long Island do I have to pay city income tax?",
  "response": "Yes, if you live in NYC and work on Long Island, you are subject to NYC income tax.\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **NYC Residency:** NYC income tax is based on residency, not where you work. If your primary residence is in one of the five boroughs of New York City (Manhattan, Brooklyn, Queens, the Bronx, or Staten Island), you must pay NYC income tax, regardless of where your income is earned.\n*   **Commuting Out of the City:** The location of your job outside of NYC does not exempt you from this tax.\n*   **Tax Forms:** You will typically report your income and calculate your NYC income tax liability when you file your New York State income tax return.\n\nIn summary, since you live in NYC you're required to pay NYC income tax regardless of the location of your employment.",
